               <msContents>
                  <summary>Introduction to a treatise on the calendar by Josiah b. Mevoraḵ al-ʿĀqūlī, which claims that the Jewish calendar repeats itself exactly every 247 years. The introduction is followed by a critique of the 247-year cycle composed by Joseph b. Āraḥ (first half of the 12th century), copied in the hand of Joseph b. Jacob ha-Bavli.</summary>
                  <msItem n="1">                           

                     <title>Calendrical</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="jrb" otherLangs="">Judaeo-Arabic (isolated Tiberian vocalisation)</textLang>
